OL,3,CRival protests underway in London as
OL,4,Cmassive police operation in place
OL,6,FMeanwhile, Daniel Kebede, National
OL,7,FEducation Union general secretary,
OL,8,Fsaid "we're marching today to show
OL,9,Fthat we will not allow Tommy Robinson
OL,10,Fand the far right to divide our
OL,11,Fcommunities".
OL,13,FJustice Secretary David Lammy said
OL,14,Fauthorities would act "swiftly" if
OL,15,Fprotests turned violent.
OL,17,FIn a post on X on Saturday, he said:
OL,18,F"The Unite the Kingdom march
OL,19,Forganisers are spreading hatred and
OL,20,Fdivision.
OL,26,@pD@FOUsD@LO]vD@WOUvD@_O]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
